# Retail Optimization Using Association Rule Mining

This project analyzes customer purchasing behavior using **Association Rule Mining (ARM)** techniques to provide actionable insights for retailers. It focuses on discovering frequently bought-together product combinations to optimize store layout, promotions, inventory, and recommendations.

## Project Owner
- **Student Name:** V.J. Kavipriya  
- **Register Number:** 422523104045  
- **Institution:** University College Of Engineering, Villupuram  
- **Department:** Information Technology  
- **Date of Submission:** 06-05-2025  

## GitHub Repository
[Visit Repository](https://github.com/kavipriyavj/projects-phase-3-kavipriya-)

---

## Project Objectives
- Discover frequent itemsets in transaction data.
- Generate association rules using Apriori algorithm.
- Recommend product bundling and shelf optimization.
- Enhance targeted promotions using data-driven insights.
- Improve stock planning and customer satisfaction.

---

## Dataset
- **Name:** Online Retail Dataset  
- **Source:** UCI Machine Learning Repository / Kaggle  
- **Size:** ~541,909 transactions, 8 features  
- **Data Type:** Structured (CSV)

---

